FBIS4-17267 "drsov078_f_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 National Affairs Small Business Sector Increases Output Small Business Sector Increases Output LD2104105194 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0737 GMT 21 Apr 94 LD2104105194 Kiev UNIAR Ukrainian BFN [Summary] Kiev, 20 Apr -- Ukraine's deputy minister of the economy, Yuriy Yekhanurov, informed journalists at a meeting of the Market Reform Press Club about the results of Ukraine's economic activity in the first quarter of this year. He said the decline in production amounts to 38.4 percent and expenditure from the state budget exceeds income by 5 trillion karbovantsi. There are currently 93,100 unemployed persons in Ukraine, while so-called hidden unemployment is about 4 million persons. He also said that small businesses manufactured 1.4-times more products in the first quarter of 1994 than in the corresponding period of last year.
